---------------------------------------------------------------
Guide for Building and Packaging the Windows Blackfin Toolchain
---------------------------------------------------------------

Generate the Blackfin toolchain to run on Windows.  See this document:
	http://docs.blackfin.uclinux.org/doku.php?id=toolchain:canadian-cross

Install the Nullsoft Scriptable Install System:
	http://nsis.sourceforge.net/
Either install a version from your distribution or compile it yourself.
Once you have a copy on your Linux machine, create the following directories:
	out-elf
	out-uclinux
	out-linux-uclibc
Then run:
 $ makensis toolchain.nsi
This will produce the Windows installer automatically.  It may take a while
to compress all of the files.

Finally, run the installer on an actual Windows machine to make sure
everything is OK.
